## Blog Content Format

Blog posts are `.md` files with YAML front matter followed by an **HTML body** (not markdown). The body uses raw `<h2>`, `<h3>`, `<p>`, `<a>`, `<strong>`, `<ul>`, `<li>` tags etc. The `blog.ts` `parsePostFile()` function uses `gray-matter` to split front matter from content, then pipes the HTML body through `addHeadingIds()` before storing as `contentHtml`.

### Front Matter

```yaml
title: "Post Title"
slug: "post-slug"
canonical: "https://domain/blog/[category-slug/]slug"
metaTitle: "SEO Title | Brand"         # MUST be under 60 chars
metaDescription: "Description"         # MUST be under 155 chars
category: "Category Name"
date: "2026-04-01"
author: "Brand Editorial Team"
image: ""
altText: "Alt text for images"
h1: "Page Heading"
summary: "Brief summary"
schema: ""
faqs:
  - question: "..."
    answer: "..."
```

## Critical: slugifyCategory Differences

**Property & Dentists** replace `&` with `and`:
```
"Section 24 & Tax Relief" ‚Üí "section-24-and-tax-relief"
"VAT & compliance" ‚Üí "vat-and-compliance"
```

**Solicitors** strips `&` entirely:
```
"SRA Compliance & Trust Accounting" ‚Üí "sra-compliance-trust-accounting"
"VAT & Compliance" ‚Üí "vat-compliance"
```

**Medical** replaces `&` with `and` (same as Property/Dentists). Uses flat post URLs (/blog/{slug}) but category hub pages exist at /blog/{category-slug}/.

